    "Unknown": "And in pain (kai basanizomen\u00ea). \"And tormented\" (present passive [v_Rev_9_5] participle of basaniz\u00f4, for which see already Rev 9:5; Rev 11:10), only here in N.T. in sense of childbirth. To be delivered (tekein). Second aorist active infinitive of tikt\u00f4, to give birth, epexegetical [v_Rev_12_4] use. Also in verse Rev 12:",
