    "Ruckman, Dr. Peter S_": "takes place (vs. 32). [v_Gen_15_13] The `[group_Canaanites_Gen_10]` question is how long is a \u201cgeneration\u201d? In Genesis 15:13, [v_Psa_90_10] it is 100 years; in\nPsalm 90:10, it is 70 years; in Matthew 1:17, it works out to about 42 years. As of this writing (2012), it is quite obvious that the generation that saw the rebirth of Israel cannot be 42 years, for that would have put the Second Advent at",
    "Unknown": "It has not come yet, but it is coming, and the hope of it should be a spur to missionary activity and zeal. The word megas [v_Rev_12_3] (great) occurs here with drak\u00f4n as in Rev 12:3, and the whole [v_Rev_20_2] picture is repeated in Rev 20:",
    "A New and Concise Bible Dictionary": "David `[char_David_Rut_4]` and Absalom both used this stratagem. 1 Sam. 26: 4; 2 Sam. 15: 10; cf. Judges 1:",
    "Commentary Vol. 83": "Wherefore he called that place Beersheba, etc.] Either Abraham `[char_Abraham_Exo_17]` or Abimelech, or both, called it so; or it may be read impersonally, \u201ctherefore the place was called Beersheba\u201d f1240, for two reasons, one implied, the other expressed; one was, because of the seven lambs before mentioned; so the Targum of Jonathan, \u201cand therefore he called the well the well of seven lambs;\u201d \u201cBeer\u201d signifying a well, and \u201csheba\u201d seven; the other, and which is more certain, being expressed, is as follows; because there they sware both of them; by the living God, to keep the covenant inviolably they had made between them.\nVer.",
    "Commentary Vol. 84": "To what position was he promoted in the kingdom?\n31. The meaning of &quot;And Pharaoh took off his ring and put it on Joseph `[char_Joseph_Ref]`'s hand&quot;?"
